  "target_response": {
    "text": "Your average isn't the problem — the timing is. Last night's 6.7 hours is right on your 7-day average of 6.7 hours, but your consistency score of 61% shows how much your bedtime swings night to night, and irregular timing degrades sleep quality even when the hours look stable. There's also a duration gap underneath: both numbers run short of your sleep need of 7.4 hours. Two moves: pick a bedtime window and hold it within about 30 minutes nightly, weekends included, and anchor your wake time first, since it's the stronger lever. Re-check the consistency score in two weeks; if it climbs while the hours hold, the feeling-off should fade with it.",
